car.picker.client
Class CarPoint

java.lang.Object
  car.shared.math.Point2D
      car.picker.client.CarPoint
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
public class CarPoint
extends Point2D

A point representing a car in an image. Contains location and size information, and can store a Color attribute. Supplies the draw(Surface) method for drawing itself onto a Surface.

Author:
Joshua Little

Method Detail

draw

public void draw(gwt.g2d.client.graphics.Surface ctx)
Draws this CarPoint onto the supplied Surface. Will fill a square of size CarPoint.Size.pointSize and stroke a square of size CarPoint.Size.rectSize, according to the CarPoints size. Both rectangles are drawn in the CarPoint color.

Parameters:
ctx - the Surface to draw on.
See Also:
getSize(), getColor()

onPoint

public boolean onPoint(Point2D point)
Returns true if the supplied Point2D is within the clickable area of this CarPoint. The clickable area is defined by a rectangle centered at this point with a size defined by getClickableSize().

Parameters:
point - the point to test.
Returns:
true if the point is within the clickable area, false otherwise.
